Iâ€™ve read a lot about banks and their employees in Morocco. Today, I opened an account at this bank, and I was pleasantly surprised by the service. I was assisted by a friendly employee named Khadija, who was very helpful and professional.

To open an account, you need a rental agreement for an apartment/house or a property ownership document, and a passport (for foreigners). The account can be opened in both dirhams and euros. I can receive funds from abroad in euros and then convert them to dirhams. While I cannot deposit dirhams in cash into my account, it is possible to receive dirhams via bank transfer from a Moroccan account.

Overall, the experience was very positive, especially due to Khadijaâ€™s professionalism. I highly recommend this bank if you are looking for a reliable financial institution in Morocco.
